blog.name: pokegodsandmissingno
blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.

Rewards for June are up on Patreon! This month we got:

  • Concept art for a good girl
  • Thumbnails of Chapter 7, pages 1 - 6
  • Inks of Chapter 7, pages 1 - 6
  • PSDs of Chapter 7, pages 1 - 6

If you enjoy “Nuzlocke on Ice” and enjoy bonus content, please consider becoming a patron today!

Or, if you’re more interested in a one-time donation, you can donate to my ko-fi account, instead. Every little bit helps!

Thank you to ALL of my patrons, who help me continue to make NOICE!

blog.title: Pokemon Sun, Moon and Violence
blog.description: Insanity the likes of which Alola has never seen

summary: Mallow is doing her best and when she feels she isn't Milo is there to insist ----------------------------------------- Milo:...
caption:
Mallow is doing her best and when she feels she isn’t Milo is there to insist

—————————————–

Milo: I’m sorry Mallow, I came as soon as I heard… Is he ok? Are you ok?
Mallow: I’m fine… Kou he… Milo he won’t say anything. You know how much he loves to talk
Milo: Yeah, sometimes I hug him just so he’ll stop talking ehehe… Emperor go cuddle my boy
Emp: Mreh :U

Mallow: Milo this is my fault… I should have stayed with him..! I should have… Done more. I’m a bad mom
Milo: …I don’t ever want to hear you say that again. Mallow, you couldn’t have known Keahi would’ve coerced him into what he thought would be harmless shenanigans. I’m not saying its ok what happened but its not the worst possible thing
Mallow: You’re right… I’m sorry
Milo: Its alright. Now, I haven’t heard ‘Maka in a good five minutes and that’s scaring me. Let’s go find wherever she’s decided to hide
